  </div>
<div>
    <p class="example"><img src="../images/inactive/inactive-dont.svg" alt="Example of an inactive button without adequate context" /></p>

    <div class="dont">
      <p><img src="../images/global/stop.svg" alt="Cross icon indicating a bad choice" /> Donâ€™t</p>
    </div>

    <figcaption>Show inactive elements without adequate context.</figcaption>
  </div>
</div>

<p>The components that can have an inactive state are:</p>

<ul>
  <li>buttons</li>
  <li>checkboxes</li>
  <li>dropdown buttons</li>
  <li>input fields</li>
  <li>radio buttons.</li>
</ul>

<h2 id="style">Style</h2>

<div class="grid-2">

  <p>Apply a 40% alpha channel to typography, icons, buttons, or components when the feature or the interface element is inactive.</p>

  <p class="example"><img src="../images/inactive/inactive-style.svg" alt="Style of an inactive button" /></p>
</div>
